  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "When you purchase an item through Krazybee, the payment of installments typically depends on the financing terms you agreed to at the time of purchase. Here are the general steps you might follow to pay your installments:\n\n1. **Review Agreement**: Check the terms and conditions of your purchase agreement with Krazybee to understand your installment plan, payment due dates, interest rates, and any penalties for late payments.\n\n2. **Payment Methods**: Krazybee would offer various payment methods, such as online banking, UPI, credit/debit cards, or mobile wallets. Make sure to use the method that works best for you.\n\n3. **Payment Schedule**: Note the schedule for your payments. This may be weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly. Setting reminders for these dates can help you stay on track.\n\n4. **Krazybee App/Website**: You can typically make payments through the Krazybee app or website. Log in to your account to view your installment payment options.\n\n5. **Customer Support**: If you have any questions or issues with your payments, don\u2019t hesitate to reach out to Krazybee\u2019s customer support for assistance.\n\n6. **Keep Records**: After making a payment, keep your receipt or confirmation as a record. This can be helpful in case of any discrepancies in the future.\n\nAlways make sure to follow their specific instructions, as procedures may vary based on the item purchased and the financing options chosen.",
